spanGrp.span: ‘I saw in the computer that there was a man and a tree;
(_) Yís të sũã'-ra jeska pe tebeli_yaga jãrga pekaga kalu je nẽ kal gate
Bá kã' juela jiebi nẽ jeska rö
There was also a big river, the mountain looks blue;
Keanẽ diglö blali tã'ĩ kabata juer siu
kabata juer tã'ĩ kabata juer siu
There, children were running barefoot at the river side;
Kea jeska je peyaba/ peyabla julur-gẽ klö pawöyiga julur-gẽ diglö kömẽ
at the river side they run.
The man brings down oranges for them,
chi/ (_) pekaga të china bötse-gẽ ĩã
am here where we live, teaching this lady our language.
se sẽr-gẽ s-kakirinã pemina yuwö se ktö' wa se ktö' wa se je të í she (m)
She does not understand how we speak, bus she is studying it.
jie ka ĩã í kser Tara jie jẽk yuwö-gẽ
I tell her extactly what went on [in the video].
Yís të jirö kable she-gẽ ĩã rö wömõĩnã wajebö mẽnẽ í köũ bi wajebö
I do not lie to her.
Ka yís rö kayuwö ta í jugömẽ kunã(m)
I tell her everything perfectly right.
Yís të jirö she ĩã rö báwã báwã köũ ñawösiga ñawösiga
Thus I saw that the place looks nice.
Jebi yís të í sũẽ (m) kã' juela bá
The man was with a thick beard;
Pekaga dul pekaga kalu (m) gugö kö ñãn e-lë-wã köũ (_) chãkãrbë
that is the one who was painting the tree.
je nẽ kalu í yuwö rö kal pachõ-glö
So, we are now studying here.
Jebi jiska sa kajali ña yuwö
There is a lot of sunshine.
And she is sitting in front of me;
So our language has a great value.
Jewa jewa ra jebi nẽ (_) se ktö' sigei rö tã'ĩ
It won’t die out; we take it along [wherever we go].
ka se ktö' shenã se/ se ktö' nẽ mẽ se da-mĩu-lo
Thus I saw that the place looks nice.
Jebí sũã' yís të-ra (m) kã' juela bá
At the distance you can see the river.
The children run and eat fruits,
and it all looks very nice.
kable juer rö bá rama köũ
I am chatting with her here.
S-kajki ĩã jiska kapagö í ra
I see that one does not make mistakes when telling things.
Yís sũã'-ra ka se kulinã-wã ta (_) jirö pagö kuna
jebi pagá je yís të jie ĩã
